-- Polish Stocks: Bank BGZ, Mostostal Warszawa Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i   a n d   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-04-12T16:09:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/polish-stocks-bank-bgz-mostostal-warszawa-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  gained 1.2
percent to 2,278.48, its highest close since April 3.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Bank Gospodarki Zywnosciowej SA (BGZ)  , the Polish unit
of Rabobank Groep, jumped 52 percent to 71.35 zloty, a record
high, after the biggest Dutch mortgage lender offered to buy the
remaining 40 percent stake in the company.  Mostostal Warszawa SA (MSW)  , the Polish construction
company controlled by Spain’s Acciona SA, gained 0.7 percent to
14.75 zloty, the first advance in more than a week after the
builder won a 666.2 million-zloty ($209 million) contract to
build a waste-to-energy project.  To contact the reporter on this story:
